        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1933198298" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8401324432443684256">The structure of this book is kind of bizarre and it feels a bit like reading a string of writing exercises by a promising young writer. The segments are in first person stream of consciousness, diary entries, third person and maybe another. But almost the entire 2nd half is 3rd person which feels like the beginning was just an experiment and then she decided to finish it up more conventionally. The book focuses much more on drug use and romantic relationship problems than the movie does, which </span>
  <span id="freeText8401324432443684256" style="display:none">The structure of this book is kind of bizarre and it feels a bit like reading a string of writing exercises by a promising young writer. The segments are in first person stream of consciousness, diary entries, third person and maybe another. But almost the entire 2nd half is 3rd person which feels like the beginning was just an experiment and then she decided to finish it up more conventionally. The book focuses much more on drug use and romantic relationship problems than the movie does, which was disappointing to me as her career frustrations and relationship with her hysterical mother are my favorite parts of the movie. Her mother is barely in the book which is a tragedy. Also, minor spoilers for book and movie but I'll hide them anyway: <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[the movie ends with her getting sober and her CAREER back on track while the book ends with her getting a nice boyfriend and her love life back on track.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> which I thought was super lame and a way better in the movie than the book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8401324432443684256" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


